cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.SY, cs.GT, cs.CE 

This paper involves optimization and decision-making in the context of smart grids, which suggests that it could belong to several sub-categories. The use of genetic algorithms for optimization suggests that it could belong to cs.LG (Machine Learning), while the modeling of customer behavior and market constraints suggests that it could also belong to cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.SY (Systems and Control). The focus on pricing and profit maximization suggests that it could belong to cs.GT (Game Theory), and the consideration of realistic market constraints suggests that it could also belong to cs.CE (Computational Economics and Finance).
